@DATABASE "pgmtoppm.guide"
@INDEX "ImageEditor.guide/INDEX"
@FONT helvetica.font 13
@SMARTWRAP

@NODE MAIN "ImageEditor - Converter: GreyToColor [pgmtoppm]"
@TOC "Converter.guide/MAIN"

@{LINDENT 4}
@{PAR}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}GreyToColor@{UB}@{FG TEXT}@{LINE}
@{PAR}@{B}Colorize a portable graymap into a portable pixmap.@{UB}@{LINE}
@{PAR}Reads a portable graymap as input. Colorizes it by multiplying the gray values by specified color or colors,
and produces a portable pixmap as output.@{LINE}
@{PAR}If only one color is specified, black in the pgm file stays black and white in the pgm file turns into the specified color in the ppm file.
If two colors are specified, then black gets mapped to the first color and white gets mapped to the second.@{LINE}
@{PAR}You can also specify an entire colormap to be used.
The mapfile is just a ppm file; it can be any shape, all that matters is the colors in it and their order.
In this case, black gets mapped into the first color in the map file, and white gets mapped to the last.@{LINE}
@{PAR}See also @{" ColorToGrey " LINK "ppmtopgm.guide/MAIN"}.@{LINE}
@{PAR}[@{B}pgmtoppm@{UB}] @{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{I}Copyright (C) 1991 by Jef Poskanzer @{UI}@{FG TEXT}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE
